title: Akki Jaanbaaz
subTitle: Akki, a young boy, juggles his life as a student and a superhero. He embarks on various adventures and helps those around him.

title: Ninja Hattori
subTitle: A little ninja, Hattori Kanzo, befriends a lazy 10-year-old boy named Kenichi Mitsuba. Hattori helps Kenichi with his problems while watching over him.

title: Roro aur Hero, Bhoot Mast, Zabardast!
subTitle: Roro, a ten year old boy gets into problematic situations in his life and is rescued by his ghost friend Hero who uses his powers to help him but makes the situation more chaotic.

title: Krishna Balram
subTitle: Krishna and his older brother Balram share a playful and loving sibling bond. Together they embark on thrilling adventures and daring escapades with Radha.

title: Krishna In Vrindavan
subTitle: In order to evade the dangers in Gokul, Krishna, along with his family, settles in Vrindavan, where he defeats the demons sent by his uncle.

title: Luv Kushh And The Ghost Army
subTitle: Twin brothers Luv and Kushh protect a baby named Narad from an army of ghosts who plan to kidnap him in order to become human again.

title: Krishna & Balram Warrior Princess
subTitle: When Krishna and Balram accidentally expose the secret hideout of a princess, they decide to protect and help her defeat her enemies.

title: Krish Trish Baltiboy 1
subTitle: Three adorable minstrels, Krish the monkey, Trish the cat and Baltiboy the donkey, collectively narrate folk tales from different regions of India.

title: Krish Trish Baltiboy 2
subTitle: Krish, Trish and Baltiboy, the three minstrels, visit various states in India in order to revisit some of the popular folk tales from the Indian culture.

title: Mighty Raju vs Mighty Clone
subTitle: Mighty Raju embarks on an adventure to catch hold of his clone who is on a spree to destroy the peace and harmony of the city of Aryanagar.

title: Akki Jaanbaaz Dhamakedaar
subTitle: Akki is a nine-year-old boy blessed with extraordinary karate skills. While he tries to lead a normal life, he ensures the optimum usage of his power for good deeds.
